-- Russian Crude Exports Dropped 1.2% Last Year, Ministry Data Show
-- B y   J a k e   R u d n i t s k y
-- 2012-01-10T09:37:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/russian-crude-exports-dropped-1-2-last-year-ministry-data-show.html
Russian crude  exports  dropped 1.2
percent in 2011 as domestic refining increased in the world’s
largest oil-producing nation.  Exports reached 266 million metric tons, or 5.34 million
barrels a day, last year, according to preliminary data from the
Energy Ministry’s CDU-TEK unit released on Jan. 2.  Exports to the  Commonwealth of Independent States  were 30
million tons. Shipments excluding the CIS were 211 million tons
via OAO Transneft’s pipelines and 25 million tons outside of the
national oil pipe operator’s system.  Production climbed 1.3 percent last year to an average of
10.27 million barrels a day, according to CDU-TEK.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jake Rudnitsky in Moscow 
